  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Inheriting from `Crowdsale` means `Finalizable` is not generic or reusable.\r\n\r\nMy use case is needing a `Crowdsale` that doesn't use a `MintableToken`, but instead uses a `StandardToken`. Since use of a `MintableToken` is hard coded into `Crowdsale` I can't use `Crowdsale` for my use case.\r\n\r\nThat alone is not such a big deal, but I also can't use anything the inherits from `Crowdsale`; doing so would require an excessive amount of overrides. \r\n\r\nIf `FinalizableCrowdsale` was simply `Finalizable` (same contract without the dependency on `Crowdsale`), I could do my custom crowdsale contract without copying and pasting the finalizable logic.",
